cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on collecting and analyzing data from social media platforms related to the 2013 German Bundestag elections. The paper discusses the data collection procedures, data description, and issues for archiving and dissemination of social media data. The paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper focuses on social media communication related to the 2013 German Bundestag elections and discusses possibilities for research with the collected data set. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses issues for archiving and dissemination of social media data, which is relevant to the intersection of computing and society. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software engineering aspects related to data collection and analysis from social media platforms. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper may involve information retrieval techniques for collecting and analyzing data from social media platforms. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper may involve natural language processing techniques for analyzing social media data.
